That’s one of several storms threatening to hamper the near record number of Americans getting a jump on their travel plans this Thanksgiving. Meteorologist Jeff Berardelli gives the forecast.
title: Series of storms threatens holiday travel across country

description: Tom Hanks sits down with Gayle King to talk about his new film "A Beautiful Day in the Neighborhood."
title: Tom Hanks' extended interview with Gayle King

description: During a concert in Boston, one fan was so moved, he yelled "wow!" The reaction surprised everyone. Steve Hartman shares his story on the road.
title: Classical concert wows young fan with autism

description: Two marathon runners have finished their 500 mile journey from Cape Cod to Arlington National Cemetery. They're raising awareness about veteran suicides.
title: Runners raising awareness for veteran suicide arrive in Arlington

description: Help is on the way for a couple from Georgia who said they're being held hostage in a hospital in Mexico. Stephen Johnson needed treatment after he went into diabetic shock while on a cruise. Mark Strassmann reports.
title: Tyler Perry helps couple held "captive" in Mexican hospital

description: A key figure in the impeachment inquiry is giving indications he might be willing to tell what he knows about aid to Ukraine. Nancy Cordes explains why everyone wants to hear from John Bolton, President Trump's former national security adviser.
title: John Bolton breaks his silence on Twitter

description: A young woman in Massachusetts is accused of urging her boyfriend to take his own life. During her arraignment, a prosecutor read dozens of disturbing text messages that were sent to him. Mola Lenghi reports.
title: Texts read in court during woman's arraignment for boyfriend's suicide

description: Some of the Trump administration officials who testified at the impeachment hearings have now gone back to work, including Lieutenant Colonel Alexander Vindman. Paula Reid has details on how the White House is retaliating against them.
title: Will Vindman be forced from his job after his impeachment testimony?

description: People in 16 states stretching from coast to coast are sick after eating romaine lettuce tainted with E. coli. At least 40 people have gotten sick. Jamie Yuccas reports.
title: E. coli outbreak linked to romaine lettuce from California

description: Storms could mess up Thanksgiving travel plans for people across the country. CBS New York's chief weathercaster Lonnie Quinn is tracking the forecast.
title: Tracking the holiday forecast

description: After years of addiction, a Louisiana man got an implant while in prison to help fight his opioid cravings. He says it changed his life. WWL-TV's Meg Farris reports from New Orleans.
title: Medical implant takes aim at opioid addiction

description: Freshman Congressman Max Rose, a Democrat from New York, talks about his service in Afghanistan in the U.S. Army, the Army National Guard, and the impeachment hearings, as well as his experience taking on the role of elected official, on this week's episode of "The Takeout with Major Garrett."
title: Representative Max Rose on "The Takeout" — 11/22/19

description: Two runners are nearing the end of their 500-mile journey to raise awareness about veterans' suicide risk. CBS News national correspondent Errol Barnett joins CBSN with more on the issue.
title: Two runners take 500-mile journey for veteran suicide awareness

description: The NFL upheld Browns defensive end Myles Garrett's indefinite suspension following an onfield brawl. And in college basketball, the NCAA suspended Memphis star James Wiseman for 12 games and ordered him to pay more than $11,000 to charity. CBS Sports HQ's Bill Reiter joins CBSN to discuss the biggest news in sports.
title: NFL upholds indefinite suspension for Browns' Myles Garrett

description: This boy with autism had been too nervous to meet Santa — until this year, when St. Nick's sweet act brought him tears of joy.
title: Santa calms boy with autism

description: Dan Raviv, senior Washington correspondent for i24 News, joins CBSN to discuss the three-year investigation of Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu that has lead to charges of fraud and accepting bribes.
title: Benjamin Netanyahu faces corruption charges

description: Inyoung You, the 21-year-old woman accused of urging her boyfriend Alexander Urtula to kill himself via text, pleaded not guilty in Boston court Friday.
title: Woman accused of urging boyfriend's suicide via text pleads not guilty

description: Members of Parliaments respond to UN Women’s Call to Action to achieve an equal world for women and men via legislation and parliamentary work, at the 2019 Women Leaders Global Forum in Reykjavik, Iceland.
title: 2019 Women Leaders Global Forum: National delegation delivers statements

description: Student advocate and #Girl2Leader Delegate Mariana Frenk Knaul sets the scene in Wednesday's first session on gender based violence at the 2019 Women Leaders Global Forum in Reykjavik, Iceland.
title: Student advocate sets the scene at 2019 Women Leaders Global Forum

description: The photo of Oscar and Valeria Ramirez, the father and daughter who drowned crossing the Rio Grande to the U.S., was seen around the world. Tania Avalos, their wife and mother, talks about her family, their journey and how it ended for the first time. "60 Minutes" reports, Sunday.
title: How Tania Avalos wants you to remember her family

description: The Justice Department official overseeing the case against 12 Russian intelligence agents who were indicted for hacking the 2016 election says he believes he could prove the agents' guilt before a jury. 60 Minutes reports, Sunday
title: Justice Department officials say they have no doubt Russians interfered in 2016 election

description: Senator Cory Booker has received $650,000 in donations since the Democratic presidential debate in Atlanta, according to his campaign. However, he still needs to do better in the polls to qualify for December's debate. Booker's national press secretary Sabrina Singh joined "CBSN AM" to discuss the state of the campaign.
title: Cory Booker raises $650K after Democratic debate in Atlanta

description: A new report in The Atlantic explores how social media is allowing the rapid spread of hatred through algorithms. NYU social psychologist Jonathan Haidt  joined CBSN to discuss how technology is enabling divisions in the U.S. instead of bringing people together.
title: How social media enables divisions instead of fostering connections

description: Google and Snapchat revealed their political ad policies this week, and Twitter made tweaks to its own rules. This comes as Facebook faces increasing backlash over its handling of political ads. Axios media reporter Sara Fischer joined CBSN to discuss.
title: Google, Snapchat update political ad policies ahead of 2020 election

description: President Trump has pushed back against House Democrats in an interview on "Fox & Friends," maintaining his position that he did nothing wrong concerning Ukraine. This comes after Democrats and Republicans on the House Intelligence Committee made their closing arguments at the end of the second week of public hearings in the impeachment inquiry. CBS News chief congressional correspondent Nancy Cordes, CBS News White House correspondent Weijia Jiang and CBS News legal analyst Kim Wehle joined CBSN to recap the week's hearings.
title: Trump pushes back against impeachment inquiry after second week of public hearings

description: Two Astronauts performed one of the most challenging spacewalks in NASA history Friday morning. It's the second in a series of high-stakes spacewalks to save a critical, $2 billion science experiment on the International Space Station. Janet Shamlian reports.
title: Astronauts conduct challenging spacewalk to fix experiment

description: Patrick Frazee has been sentenced to life in prison in Colorado for murdering his fiancee Kelsey Berreth last year. In a remarkable video, the prosecution's star witness, Krystal Lee, shows investigators how she says she helped clean up the crime scene. CBS News correspondent Nikki Battiste joined "CBSN AM" to discuss her report for "48 Hours," which airs Saturday, November 23, at 10/9c on CBS.
title: Krystal Lee showed investigators how she helped clean up murder of Kelsey Berreth
